    {
      "id": "INTERNATIONAL_PAYROLL",
      "reason": "INTERNATIONAL_PAYROLL spoke handle exists but maps to GLOBAL_PAYROLL app internally. The International Payroll app interface has spoke_handle='GLOBAL_PAYROLL' (rippling-main:app/international_payroll/rpk/app.py:53). No separate L2 entry; it's part of Global Payroll."
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Global Payroll and Payroll are distinct apps. PAYROLL spoke is US domestic payroll, GLOBAL_PAYROLL spoke handles both international and merged US+Global scenarios.",
    "My Pay (MYPAY_DUMMY_APP) shows for both employee and admin personas depending on payroll installation state.",
    "Job Codes (JOB_CODES_APP_ID) and Tax Filings (TAX_FILINGS_APP_ID) are dummy apps in FINANCE_SUBCATEGORY with stub icons/paths - visibility is not gated in dummy_apps.py (no is_visible lambda), so visibility logic must be elsewhere.",
    "Accounting Integrations appears in FINANCE subcategory and uses NavigationSubcategory.FINANCE (rippling-main:app/accounting_integrations/rpk/app.py:97-100).",
    "Spend apps (My Finances, Finance Overview) are in FINANCE_SUBCATEGORY but gated by SPENDMANAGEMENT spoke.",
    "Global Contractor (Contractor Hub) is registered under HR subcategory in RPK (rpk/app.py line 60: NavigationSubcategory.HR) but spoke is GLOBAL_CONTRACTOR.",
    "Navigation structure uses subcategories (FINANCE_SUBCATEGORY_NAME = 'navigation_bar_subcategory.finance') which map apps within the Finance category.",
    "Full Admin sees all payroll-related apps if they have corresponding permissions. My Pay visibility depends on is_my_pay_visible_for_role which checks role.isPayrollRole() or isGlobalPayrollEnabledForRole(role).",
    "Permissions checked: PAYROLL requires payroll_admin privilege, GLOBAL_PAYROLL requires GLOBAL_PAYROLL_ADMIN permission with allow_partial_scope=True."
  ]
}
